flowRoot.flowPara: Are you a developer? Register now to submit an application to the store.
Must be at least 6 characters in length
Must be at least 8 characters in length and contain numbers or punctuation
When "Sign Up for Free" is pressed, content in blue area is replaced (ideally with a nice animated transition).
Guidance is shown when user name field is focused. Disappears when another field is focused and the condition has been matched (so should remain if the user name is shorter than 6 characters).
Guidance for the email address is a bit tenuous.
Guidance text for the password field (the exact policy is a guess).
Must be at least 8 characters in length and contain numbers or punctuation
Check mark indicates when a field is completed successfully. If the email address doesn't contain an @, guidance text should read "Email address must contain an @ symbol".
Guidance text for the password field (the exact policy is a guess)
That user name is already registered

Guidance is shown when user name field is focused. If the entered user name has already been registered, guidance text should change to "That user name is already registered". This should remain even if the user name field isn't focused.
That user name is already registered. Please try another.
Must be a unique address that hasn't been registered previously
Sign up button becomes sensitive once the fields have been completed an passed initial validation (length of user name, length and composition of password).

When Sign Up is pressed, further validation is performed. If there's an error, the field is highlighted and error text shown next to it. The sign up button is made insensitive and only becomes insensitive once the field has been modified.
"That user name is already registered. Please try another."
"User names should only contain letters, dashes and underscores"
"That email address is already registered. Have you forgotten your password?"
